.TH "mx3fb_pan_display" 9 "mx3fb_pan_display" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mx3fb_pan_display \- pan or wrap the display
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mx3fb_pan_display
.BI "(struct fb_var_screeninfo *var "  ","
.BI "struct fb_info *fbi "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "var" 12
variable screen buffer information.
.IP "fbi" 12
framebuffer information pointer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
We look only at xoffset, yoffset and the FB_VMODE_YWRAP flag
